Italy’s Grilli Gets Mandate to Negotiate Greek Writedown Plan

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   S t e a r n s
-- 
2011-10-22T06:56:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-22/italy-s-grilli-gets-mandate-to-negotiate-greek-writedown-plan.html
Italy’s Vittorio Grilli was given
the mission by euro-area finance ministers to negotiate deeper
writedowns with investors on Greek debt in a second aid package,
Austrian Finance Minister Maria Fekter said. Fekter spoke to
reporters today in Brussels before a meeting of European Union
finance chiefs. She declined to give details of the mandate for
Grilli, who is head of the EU’s Economic and Finance Committee
and director general of the Italian Treasury.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan Stearns in Brussels at 
